description:
Replace k_panic() at line 437 (driver buffer overflow) with crash info storage.

Current:
  if (ret > (int)sizeof(rx_buf)) {
      LOG_ERR("CRITICAL: lora_recv returned %d > buffer");
      k_panic();
  }

This case is special: if the driver returned more bytes than buffer size, stack corruption may have already occurred. But panicking still makes the device unresponsive.

Target:
  if (ret > (int)sizeof(rx_buf)) {
      LOG_ERR("lora_l2: driver overflow (%d > %d)", ret, sizeof(rx_buf));
      store_crash_info(CRASH_DRIVER_OVERFLOW, __LINE__, ret);
      atomic_set(&current_state, LORA_ABORTED);
      return;  // Let watchdog reset us
  }

Requires: crash_info retained RAM infrastructure (separate task).
